Borussia Dortmund and RB Salzburg have opened negotiations for Karim Adeyemi. Borussia Dortmund have opened talks with RB Salzburg for Karim Adeyemi, according to Sky Germany. According to Sky, BVB sporting director Michael Zorc and his successor, current head of first team football Sebastian Kehl were spotted at Dortmund airport on Monday after returning from Salzburg. It has been reported that Adeyemi has already agreed personal terms with Dortmund, but ‘Die Schwarzgelben’ are yet to agree a transfer fee with Salzburg. RB Salzburg are said to be demanding €30-40 million for the 20-year-old striker, who has scored 18 goals in 28 games this season.